fields.title: My first Rosetta
fields.description: This is my very first rosetta, it was slightly complicated but after a while I got the hang of it. I want to make sure I try different shapes from here on! I cant wait to share this journey with you guys and I cant wait to see what everyone else comes up with

fields.title: Tulip Triumph
fields.description: I finally got a tulip, with this one I had to dip further into my crema than expected. I found if my hand was shaky recovery wouldn't be as difficult as I thought initially.

fields.title: Lots of Love
fields.description: Okay, so it turns out hearts are my favorite, they're easy, straightforward, and really hard to mess up. Plus everyone could use a little love lol.

fields.title: Graceful Swan
fields.description: So far this has been the most complicated art I've attempted. I messed up with the initial dip and slice. I got this one but it was low-kwy just good luck. HOPEFULLY, I can perfect it soon.

fields.title: Rosie
fields.description: So I may be competing for favorite between Hearts and Rosetta's,the plant aspect is visually appealing to me.

fields.title: Delicate Tulip
fields.description: Who doesn't love a tulip? Simple, classic, and beautiful.

fields.title: Fly Away
fields.description: Can swans fly? Well this one cannot but shes gorgeous regardless

fields.title: Key to my ...
fields.description: Lol not much to say here, just some loveeeee.

fields.title: Something Different
fields.description: YAYYYY, my first cup of cross art! This took so much patience and technique. It took about a gazillion tries but I just needed to stick with it, I hope you guys like it. A heart and a tulip!
